    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Schools and Pipe Dreams</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael L Harper reply to Apr 30 letter holds teachers' union would never allow salaries to be based on performance</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How to Pay Teachers'' (letter, April 30), about dividing groups of teachers into best, average and below average in terms of performance and paying them accordingly: It will never happen, because the idea makes too much sense and would usurp the power of the teachers' union, which would not allow it to be used.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL L. HARPER  Royal Oak, Mich., April 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How to Pay Teachers'' (letter, April 30), about dividing groups of teachers into best, average and below average in terms of performance and paying them accordingly: It will never happen, because the idea makes too much sense and would usurp the power of the teachers' union, which would not allow it to be used.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL L. HARPER  Royal Oak, Mich., April 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
